This is a first program in Rails, so it has a lot of first program issues.  
For instance, I wrote the program in Ruby192, had to convert to Ruby187
to try to get it to work on dreamhost, when that didn't work, I had to
reconvert it to Ruby192 so it would work on Heroku.

Pindule is a comedy template, intended to be the web version of Dr Katz.
Dr. Katz allows comedians to work in a structure that allows them to
create comic material, and I tried to create the same structure with
Pindule.

As far as code, the only interesting part is the bit of ajax, which allows
the user to have his page refreshed when the moderator sends him a chat
reply, and the moderator has his refresh when a user enters text